OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5F'Survival was luck of the  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdraw on D-Day'             
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, One of Britain's last remaining D-Day  
OL,6, veterans has said he puts his survival 
OL,7, down to "the luck of the draw".        
OL,9,FLes Budding, 97, was 18 years old when 
OL,10,Fhe served on board Landing Craft Flak  
OL,11,F34, charged with providing covering    
OL,12,Ffire for the first wave of troops who  
OL,13,Fstormed Sword Beach on 6 June 1944.    
OL,15,FMr Budding said: "On this anniversary, 
OL,16,FI'm thinking about the veterans we've  
OL,17,Flost over the past few years.          
OL,19,F"I'm also thinking about all those men 
OL,20,Fwe lost that day."                     
